Package expressions

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Addition
    Addition is the class that extends Expression to provide a sum of two other expressions.
    Division
    Division is the class that extends Expression to provide a quotient of two other expressions.
    Expression
    Expression is the class that takes tokens from the parser and creates an object that can be evaluated.
    Integer
    Integer is the class that extends Expression to provide an integer constant value.
    Multiplication
    Multiplication is the class that extends Expression to provide a product of two other expressions.
    Parentheses
    Parentheses is the class that extends Expression to provide a parenthetical subexpression.
    Parse
    Parse is the class that breaks a string into tokens.
    Subtraction
    Subtraction is the class that extends Expression to provide a difference of two other expressions.
